main event: Radar operators at Patuxent River NAS tracked an unidentified aerial object on 17 July 1959, which was observed visually as well.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar screens at approximately 0302 EST,The object traveled at a high rate of speed making abrupt changes in direction,Several jet interceptors were scrambled to investigate but could not make visual contact,The object was reported to have been at an altitude of approximately 19,000 feet,The object disappeared from radar screens at approximately 0337 EST.
